First, git clone:

  $ git clone -b generic git@github.com:ZezhiWang/cassandra.git

Modify ip in config file

  $ conf/cassandra.yaml

Compile

  $ make

Run the instance

  $ make run
  
Clean data & log

  $ make clean

Now let's try to read and write some data using the Cassandra Query Language:

  $ bin/cqlsh <listening IP>

The command line client is interactive so if everything worked you should
be sitting in front of a prompt:

----
Connected to Test Cluster at <IP>:<port>.
[cqlsh 2.2.0 | Cassandra 1.2.0 | CQL spec 3.0.0 | Thrift protocol 19.35.0]
Use HELP for help.
cqlsh> 
----

Create Keyspace for ycsb testing

----
cqlsh> CREATE KEYSPACE ycsb 
       WITH replication = { 'class' : 'SimpleStrategy', 'replication_factor' : <number of servers> };
cqlsh> USE ycsb;
cqlsh:ycsb> CREATE TABLE usertable (
                 y_id varchar PRIMARY KEY,
                 field0 varchar,
                 z_value int,
                 writer_id varchar
               );
cqlsh:ycsb> INSERT INTO usertable (y_id, field0) 
               VALUES ('key', 'value');
cqlsh:ycsb> SELECT * FROM usertable WHERE y_id='key';
 y_id | field0 | z_value      | writer_id
---------+-----+-------+------------------
  key |  value |  <Timestamp> | <Writer ID> 
cqlsh:ycsb> 
----
